## Code Review: PR #627 — **APPROVE**

Clean, well-executed mobile polish PR. All 4 source files correctly gate changes with `md:hidden`/`hidden md:block`. No logic errors, regressions, or scope violations found.

### Findings (2 LOW)

**Finding 1 — Redundant `.toUpperCase()` (LOW/style)**
`BriefingPanel.tsx` calls `formatGreetingDate().toUpperCase()` while also applying the CSS `uppercase` class. The JS call is unnecessary — every other micro-label in this PR uses the CSS class alone. Easy one-line fix: remove the `.toUpperCase()`.

**Finding 2 — Dark and light sidebar-empty screenshots now identical (LOW/awareness)**
Before this PR they had different SHA1s; after they're identical. Root cause: `.locator('aside').first()` picks the mobile `<aside>` in the DOM, and the new avatar element renders identically in both color-scheme modes since the app is dark-only. Not a bug — the screenshots look correct on visual inspection — but the `dark-chromium` sidebar test no longer adds distinct coverage.

### CLAUDE.md Compliance
All rules pass: `safe-area-pb` preserved, no new abstractions, desktop views untouched, screenshots committed and inspected.
